Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an unparished area. See also Table 
    2, note (d).

In 1889 the part of the parish of Cliviger in Todmorden Urban 
    District became part of Yorkshire West Riding, in 1894 this area became the 
    separate parish of Cornholme, so that thereafter Cliviger was again wholly in 
    Lancashire. See also Table 2, note (c).
